text: Carns is an extinct town in Keya Paha County, in the U.S. state of Nebraska. Carns bears the name of a pioneer settler. A post office called Carns was established in 1879, and remained in operation until 1943. An early variant name of the post office may have been Elm Grove. ==References== Category:Ghost towns in Nebraska Category:Landforms of Keya Paha County, Nebraska
title: Carns, Nebraska
